  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a complex financial crime, and law enforcement and legal systems use various strategies to investigate and prosecute such schemes. Some key approaches include:\n\n1. Financial investigation techniques\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Analyzing bank records and money trails\n- Using forensic accounting methods\n- Identifying suspicious transaction patterns\n\n2. Legal frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Reporting obligations for financial institutions\n- International cooperation agreements\n\n3. Investigative tools\n- Advanced data analysis\n- Undercover operations\n- Electronic surveillance\n- Collaboration between agencies\n\n4. Prosecution strategies\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal charges\n- Financial penalties\n- International extradition\n\nThese methods help combat sophisticated money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
